			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coal is one of the most important primary fossil fuels. It is a solid carbon-rich material that is usually brown or black and most often occurs in stratified sedimentary deposits. Coal is a type of fossil fuel, formed when dead plant matter decays into peat and is converted into coal by the heat and pressure of deep burial over millions of years.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">煤炭是最重要的原生化石燃料之一。它是一种富含碳的固体物质，通常呈棕色或黑色，最常见于层状沉积矿床中。煤炭是化石燃料的一种，由死亡的植物物质腐烂成泥炭，并在数百万年的深埋热量和压力作用下转化成煤炭。</common:generalComment>
